      "suggested_fix": "Cross-reference resolution must be either: (A) precomputed at index time and stored as a field on the document (preferred — add to 'Requires backend work' column in §0), or (B) done as a single batch query after render (extract all reference patterns, fire one multi-search request, then decorate links asynchronously). Option B is acceptable for MVP but must not block initial render. Render all references as styled non-interactive text first, then upgrade to links as batch results return. Add this to the architecture and adjust the timebox."
